<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5357.2.5>
    dc:creator "Chen, Hsuan-Pu", "Lin, Kai-Ti", "Wu, Shipher" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Re-evaluation of the taxonomic confusion of the metallic-blue Pimpla Fabricius, 1804 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Pimplinae) species in the Oriental region" ;
    bibo:endPage "284" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-10-18" ;
    bibo:startPage "270" ;
    bibo:volume "5357" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018113>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018115>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018117>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018121>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018123>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018127> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018113>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–5. The holotype of Pimpla cyanea Morley, 1913 (=Pimpla cyanator Morley, 1914), NHMUK. 1, dorsal habitus; 2, face in anterior view; 3, labels; 4, lateral habitus; 5, propodeum in dorsal view. Photographed by Gavin Broad. © Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London (available under CC-BY 4.0). Scale bars: 4, 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018113/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018115>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6–11. The holotype of Coccygomimus alishanensis Kusigemati, 1984 (=Pimpla alishanensis), SEHU. 6, dorsal habitus; 7, labels; 8, face in anterior view; 9, fore coxa; 10, lateral habitus; 11, propodeum in lateral view. Photographed by Hsuan-Pu Chen. Scale bars: 3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018115/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018117>
    dc:description "FIGURES 12–17. The female of the Taiwanese Pimpla cyanator Morley, 1914, NTM. 12, lateral habitus; 13, apex of ovipositor; 14, head in dorsal view, mesoscutum and scutellum; 15, face in anterior view; 16, propodeum in dorsal view; 17, tergites I–III in dorsal view. Photographed by Hsuan-Pu Chen. Scale bars: 12, 3 mm; 13, 0.5 mm; 14–17, 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018117/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018121>
    dc:description "FIGURES 18–22. The male of the Taiwanese Pimpla cyanator Morley, 1914, TFRI. 18, lateral habitus; 19, tyloids on the male flagellomeres indicated by the white triangle; 20, face in anterior view; 21, male genitalia and hypopygium; 22, propodeum and tergite I in dorso-lateral view. Photographed by Hsuan-Pu Chen. Scale bars: 18, 3 mm; 19–21, 0.5 mm; 22, 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018121/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018123>
    dc:description "FIGURES 23–27. Variation in the Taiwanese specimens of Pimpla cyanator Morley, 1914, TFRI (23, 27), TARI (24, 26), NTM (25). 23, alcohol-treated specimen; 24, faded historical specimen; 25, female fore coxae without yellow spot; 26, female fore coxae with yellow spot indicated by the white triangle; 27, male fore coxae. Photographed by Hsuan-Pu Chen. Scale bars: 23–24, 3 mm; 25–27, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018123/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018127>
    dc:description "FIGURES 28–29. The living female Pimpla cyanator Morley, 1914 found in Syueshan giant tree, Heping, Taichung City, Taiwan. 28, a living individual; 29, a living individual searching on the moss land. Photographed by Shipher Wu. Scale bars: 28, 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018127/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

